The paper deals with the design of protocols for point-to-point wireless erasure links with unreliable and delayed feedback, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed protocols to various challenges, such as imperfect and delayed feedback, burst erasures, and round-trip time fluctuations, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
